modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and transforming structured text data, including line-by-line processing and pattern matching. Operates on strings and custom record types representing parsed elements. Used to convert log files into structured event data and to extract metadata from configuration files.

Generates OCaml code for type expressions and interpretation functors using PPX syntax extensions, handling module type declarations and structure items. Processes custom type definitions and functor expansions to produce derived modules with embedded logic. Supports test harness creation and integrates multiple derivation steps into a unified module.
